OL,6,FSome members of the public and
OL,7,Fbusiness leaders have called on unions
OL,8,Fto suspend strike action to prevent
OL,9,Ffurther impact on industry and those
OL,10,Fwho rely on public transport services.
OL,12,FIt has been suggested that calling off
OL,13,Fthe strikes would be a gesture of
OL,14,Fgoodwill recognising the progress
OL,15,Fbeing made towards Stormont's
OL,16,Frestoration.
OL,18,FPeter Macklin GMB Regional Organiser
OL,19,Fhighlighted that action remains
OL,20,Fongoing because crucially a pay offer
OL,21,Fhas not yet been put on the table.
